text: The Peek Baronetcy, of Rousdon in the County of Devon, is a title in the Baronetage of the United Kingdom. It was created on 13 May 1874 for Henry Peek. He was an importer of spices, tea and other groceries, a philanthropist and Conservative Member of Parliament for Surrey Mid. The third Baronet was High Sheriff of Devon in 1912. ==Peek baronets, of Rousdon (1874)== *Sir Henry William Peek, 1st Baronet (1825–1898) *Sir Cuthbert Edgar Peek, 2nd Baronet (1855–1901) *Sir Wilfrid Peek, 3rd Baronet (1884–1927) *Sir Francis Henry Grenville Peek, 4th Baronet (1915–1996) *Sir William Grenville Peek, 5th Baronet (1919–2004) *Sir Richard Grenville Peek, 6th Baronet (born 1955) ==Notes== ==References== *Kidd, Charles, Williamson, David (editors).
